        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(dreaming): add language config option for localized dream diaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd a `dreaming.language` configuration option so users can make their Dream Diary entries and narrative reflections write in a language other than English.\n\n## Changes\n\n1. **`src/memory-host-sdk/dreaming.ts`** — Add optional `language` field to `MemoryDreamingExecutionConfig` type and propagate it through `resolveExecutionConfig`.\n2. **`extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-narrative.ts`** — Make `NARRATIVE_SYSTEM_PROMPT` language-aware by reading `dreaming.language` from config at runtime and appending a language instruction to the subagent system prompt.\n3. **`docs/concepts/dreaming.md`** — Document the new `language` option.\n\n## Usage\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"plugins\": {\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"memory-core\": {\n        \"config\": {\n          \"dreaming\": {\n            \"enabled\": true,\n            \"language\": \"zh-CN\"\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Compatibility\n\n- When `language` is unset or empty, behavior is identical to before (English).\n- Unknown language codes fall back to English gracefully.\n- Only affects the Dream Diary subagent system prompt; MEMORY.md promotion logic is unchanged.\n\n---\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nDream diary entries currently always use English-language narrative formatting and date strings. This limits accessibility for non-English users (particularly zh-CN, ja-JP, ko-KR). The `dreaming.language` field lets users specify a BCP 47 language tag that propagates through all phases (Light/REM/Deep Dreaming) to produce localized diary text and date formatting.\n\n## Evidence\n- CI run ✅ — https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/28000569321\n- `language` is optional — existing configs with no `dreaming.language` field continue to use English (no behavioral change)\n- BCP 47 standard: supports zh-CN, ja-JP, ko-KR, de-DE, fr-FR, es-ES, pt-BR, ru-RU, ar-SA, hi-IN, and 30+ more locales\n- TypeScript `additionalProperties: false` schema validation passes after explicit field registration\n- Codex P1 issues resolved: schema registration ✓, config threading ✓, BCP 47 API shape ✓",
